    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle Street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="nyp.00545_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1886-04-12" rend="right">April 12 p m </date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Rec'd yours last week &#38; was glad as always to get letter from you<ptr
                    target="nyp.00545_n2"/>&#8212;Dr Bucke has been here&#8212;left this morning for
                N Y&#8212;sails Wednesday next for England&#8212;to stay two months&#8212;was with
                me Friday, Saturday &#38; Sunday&#8212;we rode out every day&#8212;</p>
            <p>He is pretty well&#8212;I am ab't the same as when I last wrote&#8212;am to read the
                "Death of Lincoln" lecture Thurs: afternoon next in the Phila: Chestnut St Opera
                House&#8212;the actors &#38; journalists have tendered me a sort of
                benefit&#8212;Thomas Donaldson and Talcott Williams are the instigators of it
                all&#8212;(I am receiving great &#38; opportune Kindnesses in my old
                days&#8212;&#38; this is one of them)<ptr target="nyp.00545_n3"/>&#8212;</p>
            <p>The printed slip on the other side I just cut out of my Phila: <hi rend="italic">Press</hi> of this
                    morning<ptr target="nyp.00545_n4"/>&#8212;I am looking for your little book<ptr
                    target="nyp.00545_n5"/>&#8212;Good weather here&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
